| `data-testid="user-timeline"` | ❌ absent from SSR HTML |

## Root cause

`src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` is a `"use client"` component that fetches data in `useEffect`. The initial server render hits `loading=false, profile=null` → "User not found" branch. Only `data-testid="user-profile"` is in the SSR HTML. The `identity-cluster` and `user-timeline` testids are gated on a loaded profile, which only happens client-side after hydration + fetch.

## Required fix (for Sprint 2)

Refactor `src/app/users/[id]/page.tsx` to a **Server Component**: remove `"use client"`, replace `useParams` + `useUserProfile` with an `async` page function that calls `getUserProfile()` from `@/lib/users` directly. This makes all three `data-testid` attributes present in the initial SSR HTML. `UserTimeline.tsx` needs no changes.
