Here's a summary of what was done in F32 Sprint 2:

## Changes made

**`src/lib/identity.ts`** — Added `toClickHouseTs()` helper and applied it to the event INSERT. ClickHouse DateTime64 with JSONEachRow rejects ISO 8601 `T`/`Z` suffixes; it requires `"YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.mmm"`. The returned `EventRow.timestamp` still keeps ISO format.

**`vitest.config.ts`** — Two additions:
1. `loadEnvFile()` reads `.env.local` into `test.env` so `CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD=""` is available without an explicit env override (Vitest doesn't inject non-`VITE_`-prefixed vars from `.env.local` automatically)
2. `fileParallelism: false` — `identity.integration.test.ts` and `users.integration.test.ts` both use `minipanel_test` tables; running them in parallel caused one file's `afterEach` truncate to destroy data mid-test in the other

**`src/lib/__tests__/identity.test.ts`** — Fixed 2 assertions checking the INSERT payload timestamp: updated expected value from ISO to ClickHouse format; fixed UTC-safe parsing (factual errors, not behavior changes)

**`src/lib/__tests__/users.integration.test.ts`** — Fixed `insertRawEvent` helper's hardcoded ISO timestamp to convert to ClickHouse format before inserting

**`scripts/__tests__/migrate.integration.test.ts`** — (1) omit `--password` flag when empty (ClickHouse CLI rejects `--password=`); (2) added `timeout: 3000` to `execFileSync` in the TCP/HTTP-mismatch test — the native CLI hangs ~3s connecting to HTTP port 8123

**Result: 638/638 tests pass, lint exits 0, typecheck exits 0**
